SIMPLE: ingurgitate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingurgitate
<hw>In*gur"gi*tate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ingurgitatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>ingurgitare</ets> to pour in;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>gurges</ets> whirlpool, gulf.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To swallow, devour, or drink greedily or in large
quantity; to guzzle.</def> <rj><au>Cleveland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To swallow up, as in a gulf.</def>
<rj><au>Fotherby.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingurgitate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ingurgitate
<hw>In*gur"gi*tate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To guzzle; to
swill.</def> <rj><au>Burton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingurgitation</ent>⟦br⟧
